Text.SourceString: Eh? Are ya looking for farming advice?//Never worked the land, myself. I’m more at home at sea.//’Cept for my plants, ’ere. My lovelies.
Text.LocalizedString: Eh? Are ya looking for farming advice?//Never worked the land, myself. I’m more at home at sea.//’Cept for my plants, ’ere. My lovelies.

Text.SourceString: *nods*
Text.LocalizedString: *nods*

Text.SourceString: Aye.
Text.LocalizedString: Aye.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Wataru</> is humming a sea chantey.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Wataru</> is humming a sea chantey.]

Text.SourceString: What’re you looking at?
Text.LocalizedString: What’re you looking at?

Text.SourceString: I don’t get to Starlet much. Keep to myself ’ere at the lighthouse.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t get to Starlet much. Keep to myself ’ere at the lighthouse.

Text.SourceString: I’m not too fond of people, if you want to know the truth.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not too fond of people, if you want to know the truth.

Text.SourceString: Nothing personal, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Just can’t be bothered.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing personal, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Just can’t be bothered.

Text.SourceString: You know my son, <NPCName>Wakuu</>?
Text.LocalizedString: You know my son, <NPCName>Wakuu</>?

Text.SourceString: He comes out here on weekends.//Sometimes he’s the only living soul I see all week.
Text.LocalizedString: He comes out here on weekends.//Sometimes he’s the only living soul I see all week.

Text.SourceString: Fine with me. Not complaining.
Text.LocalizedString: Fine with me. Not complaining.

Text.SourceString: Back in my fishing days, our nets were always full. Now yer lucky to get one bite all afternoon.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in my fishing days, our nets were always full. Now yer lucky to get one bite all afternoon.

Text.SourceString: I only have one mouth to feed.//But I feel for them fishermen trying to make a living these days.
Text.LocalizedString: I only have one mouth to feed.//But I feel for them fishermen trying to make a living these days.

Text.SourceString: The sea takes care of you if you take care of it.//And if you don’t…
Text.LocalizedString: The sea takes care of you if you take care of it.//And if you don’t…

Text.SourceString: Cold weather’s blowing in from the east. We’ll see some snow before long.
Text.LocalizedString: Cold weather’s blowing in from the east. We’ll see some snow before long.

Text.SourceString: Bah.
Text.LocalizedString: Bah.

Text.SourceString: Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Humph.

Text.SourceString: Holy mackerel, <PlayerName>$player</>!//You scared the barnacles off me!
Text.LocalizedString: Holy mackerel, <PlayerName>$player</>!//You scared the barnacles off me!

Text.SourceString: Don’t go sneaking up on an old man like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t go sneaking up on an old man like that.

Text.SourceString: What’re you looking at? Never seen an old man on his knees in the dirt before?
Text.LocalizedString: What’re you looking at? Never seen an old man on his knees in the dirt before?

Text.SourceString: Just because I’m an old crank doesn’t mean I can’t enjoy nature.//Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Just because I’m an old crank doesn’t mean I can’t enjoy nature.//Humph.

Text.SourceString: Did you hear something?//Like a whistling noise, coming in off the water?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you hear something?//Like a whistling noise, coming in off the water?

Text.SourceString: No? Must’ve been the wind.
Text.LocalizedString: No? Must’ve been the wind.

Text.SourceString: ’Ere’s something I like about pufferfish: they have an elastic stomach! They puff themselves up into balloons when they’re threatened.
Text.LocalizedString: ’Ere’s something I like about pufferfish: they have an elastic stomach! They puff themselves up into balloons when they’re threatened.

Text.SourceString: Not to be confused with Pufferfish, the corporation. Love the fish; can’t say the same for the company.
Text.LocalizedString: Not to be confused with Pufferfish, the corporation. Love the fish; can’t say the same for the company.

Text.SourceString: I s’pose now that Summer’s ’ere, everyone’s going to be walking around eating ice cream.//<portrait=normal>Don’t care for it, myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I s’pose now that Summer’s ’ere, everyone’s going to be walking around eating ice cream.//<portrait=normal>Don’t care for it, myself.

Text.SourceString: And so messy! Putting a food that melts on top of a cone so it can drip all over your hands in the hot sun… I just never understood the appeal.
Text.LocalizedString: And so messy! Putting a food that melts on top of a cone so it can drip all over your hands in the hot sun… I just never understood the appeal.

Text.SourceString: Some sort of critter’s been munching on my lovelies! The leaves are all riddled with tooth marks.
Text.LocalizedString: Some sort of critter’s been munching on my lovelies! The leaves are all riddled with tooth marks.

Text.SourceString: You get that on your farm too?
Text.LocalizedString: You get that on your farm too?

Text.SourceString: Summer’s the best time for fishing. In this weather, you can toss out a net and pull it in, full of fish. Easy as that!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer’s the best time for fishing. In this weather, you can toss out a net and pull it in, full of fish. Easy as that!

Text.SourceString: Legend has it there’s sunken treasure around these parts. I don’t doubt it.
Text.LocalizedString: Legend has it there’s sunken treasure around these parts. I don’t doubt it.

Text.SourceString: When a ship sinks, it takes its secrets with it.
Text.LocalizedString: When a ship sinks, it takes its secrets with it.

Text.SourceString: This time of year, the beach gets too crowded for my taste. I won’t mind when it gets cooler and all the people go away.
Text.LocalizedString: This time of year, the beach gets too crowded for my taste. I won’t mind when it gets cooler and all the people go away.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the snow. It’s the ice that irks me. Turns the water into land.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the snow. It’s the ice that irks me. Turns the water into land.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to garden with snow everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to garden with snow everywhere.

Text.SourceString: ’Ere, fishy, fishy, fishy.
Text.LocalizedString: ’Ere, fishy, fishy, fishy.

Text.SourceString: *talking to his plants* There we go, my lovelies. Stretch your leaves up to the sun…
Text.LocalizedString: *talking to his plants* There we go, my lovelies. Stretch your leaves up to the sun…

Text.SourceString: Whatever <NPCName>Jim</> made is good today.
Text.LocalizedString: Whatever <NPCName>Jim</> made is good today.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll have another.//<NPCName>Wakuu</>, have another one. You don’t eat enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll have another.//<NPCName>Wakuu</>, have another one. You don’t eat enough.

Text.SourceString: *talking to his plants* ’Ere we go, my lovelies.//Some water for you, some plant food for you…
Text.LocalizedString: *talking to his plants* ’Ere we go, my lovelies.//Some water for you, some plant food for you…

Text.SourceString: I need to go over to the Beach Shack and get some bait. Can’t fish without proper bait!
Text.LocalizedString: I need to go over to the Beach Shack and get some bait. Can’t fish without proper bait!

Text.SourceString: What d’ya think of this rain, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: What d’ya think of this rain, eh?

Text.SourceString: Must be good for your crops. My lovelies in the garden are drinking it up.
Text.LocalizedString: Must be good for your crops. My lovelies in the garden are drinking it up.

Text.SourceString: What d’ya think of this storm, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: What d’ya think of this storm, eh?

Text.SourceString: Must be good for your crops. My lovelies in the garden are drinking it up.
Text.LocalizedString: Must be good for your crops. My lovelies in the garden are drinking it up.

Text.SourceString: Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Humph.

Text.SourceString: Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Humph.

Text.SourceString: Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Humph.

Text.SourceString: Humph.
Text.LocalizedString: Humph.

Text.SourceString: ’Ave you heard the story of my tussle with the whale? No?
Text.LocalizedString: ’Ave you heard the story of my tussle with the whale? No?

Text.SourceString: This was back in my seafaring days. One day, I was sailing through a monstrous storm…//Worse than this one, even! Rain pounding down, my boat tossing around in the waves.
Text.LocalizedString: This was back in my seafaring days. One day, I was sailing through a monstrous storm…//Worse than this one, even! Rain pounding down, my boat tossing around in the waves.

Text.SourceString: And then the boat rises up, up, up out of the water. I thought we were riding a swell!//<portrait=concerned>But no! It was a whale, carrying the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> along on its back!//I held on for dear life, I did! Then the whale dipped below the surface, and we were back in the sea.//Don’t believe me? Aye, maybe you had to be there.
Text.LocalizedString: And then the boat rises up, up, up out of the water. I thought we were riding a swell!//<portrait=concerned>But no! It was a whale, carrying the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> along on its back!//I held on for dear life, I did! Then the whale dipped below the surface, and we were back in the sea.//Don’t believe me? Aye, maybe you had to be there.

Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t mind it if <NPCName>Wakuu</> ran a business like <NPCName>Suki</> and <NPCName>Alice</> at the inn.//Providing a service for the people of Coral Island – That would be noble work.
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t mind it if <NPCName>Wakuu</> ran a business like <NPCName>Suki</> and <NPCName>Alice</> at the inn.//Providing a service for the people of Coral Island – That would be noble work.

Text.SourceString: Tried to get him interested in fishing, but bah, the boy would have none of it.//From a young age, all he ever wanted to do was gaze up at the stars.
Text.LocalizedString: Tried to get him interested in fishing, but bah, the boy would have none of it.//From a young age, all he ever wanted to do was gaze up at the stars.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Wakuu’s</> been going on about the Cherry Blossom Festival. He wants me to go with him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Wakuu’s</> been going on about the Cherry Blossom Festival. He wants me to go with him.

Text.SourceString: Bah. I don’t see the point.
Text.LocalizedString: Bah. I don’t see the point.

Text.SourceString: I’ve seen the fishing change around here. Used to be we’d catch hundreds of crabs in a day.//The sea was brimming with ’em. But the waters have changed. Fewer of those fat, beautiful crabs, more bottom-feeders.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve seen the fishing change around here. Used to be we’d catch hundreds of crabs in a day.//The sea was brimming with ’em. But the waters have changed. Fewer of those fat, beautiful crabs, more bottom-feeders.

Text.SourceString: And the trash! By the end of my time on the boat, some days we’d haul up more garbage than fish.//<portrait=normal>That’s when I knew it was time to retire. Let the new generation take the helm.
Text.LocalizedString: And the trash! By the end of my time on the boat, some days we’d haul up more garbage than fish.//<portrait=normal>That’s when I knew it was time to retire. Let the new generation take the helm.

Text.SourceString: I used to catch <NPCName>Wakuu</> up on deck at night, stargazing. He’d sneak out of bed!
Text.LocalizedString: I used to catch <NPCName>Wakuu</> up on deck at night, stargazing. He’d sneak out of bed!

Text.SourceString: Finally, I stopped trying to make him stay put. The boy was obsessed with those stars, he was.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, I stopped trying to make him stay put. The boy was obsessed with those stars, he was.

Text.SourceString: Y’know that book, <Italic>The Old Man and the Sea</>? That’s my autobiography!
Text.LocalizedString: Y’know that book, <Italic>The Old Man and the Sea</>? That’s my autobiography!

Text.SourceString: Just making a little joke there, <PlayerName>$player</>. I ’aven’t even read it.
Text.LocalizedString: Just making a little joke there, <PlayerName>$player</>. I ’aven’t even read it.

Text.SourceString: I appreciate yer company, <PlayerName>$player</>. I may not be a man of many words, but…
Text.LocalizedString: I appreciate yer company, <PlayerName>$player</>. I may not be a man of many words, but…

Text.SourceString: Bah. ’Ere I go, getting sentimental.//<portrait=normal>I’m just trying to say it’s nice to chat a spell. Does get lonely around ’ere sometimes, y’know.
Text.LocalizedString: Bah. ’Ere I go, getting sentimental.//<portrait=normal>I’m just trying to say it’s nice to chat a spell. Does get lonely around ’ere sometimes, y’know.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell <NPCName>Wakuu</> I said that. He’d take it all wrong.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell <NPCName>Wakuu</> I said that. He’d take it all wrong.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> comes around to see me often enough. I’ll give the boy credit for that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> comes around to see me often enough. I’ll give the boy credit for that.

Text.SourceString: But we never have much to say. Seems we’re always butting heads, me and him.
Text.LocalizedString: But we never have much to say. Seems we’re always butting heads, me and him.

Text.SourceString: Makes me wonder if one of these days he’ll “forget” to stop by.//I raised him better than that, but kids these days just don’t respect their parents like my generation did…
Text.LocalizedString: Makes me wonder if one of these days he’ll “forget” to stop by.//I raised him better than that, but kids these days just don’t respect their parents like my generation did…

Text.SourceString: Working on a fishing boat’s no pleasure cruise, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re up all day and night, hauling nets, steering the ship, swabbing the deck.
Text.LocalizedString: Working on a fishing boat’s no pleasure cruise, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You’re up all day and night, hauling nets, steering the ship, swabbing the deck.

Text.SourceString: Aye… I miss those days.
Text.LocalizedString: Aye… I miss those days.

Text.SourceString: I had a motley crew on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. Sailors can be rough people.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a motley crew on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. Sailors can be rough people.

Text.SourceString: But sailors are like family too. We worked hard together.//When yer riding out a storm, that’s who you want at yer back – family.
Text.LocalizedString: But sailors are like family too. We worked hard together.//When yer riding out a storm, that’s who you want at yer back – family.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> spent most of his childhood on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> with me.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> spent most of his childhood on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> with me.

Text.SourceString: He wasn’t more than four years old when he hooked his first parrotfish. I was proud of him, I was.
Text.LocalizedString: He wasn’t more than four years old when he hooked his first parrotfish. I was proud of him, I was.

Text.SourceString: Don’t know where I went wrong. He would have been a fine fisherman.//<portrait=concerned>But instead, he had to go and become a <Italic>star</> scientist.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t know where I went wrong. He would have been a fine fisherman.//<portrait=concerned>But instead, he had to go and become a <Italic>star</> scientist.

Text.SourceString: I have to say, young people like you give me some hope, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say, young people like you give me some hope, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I look at you and everything you’ve done with your farm, and I think at least some of today’s young people ’ave a good head on their shoulders.
Text.LocalizedString: I look at you and everything you’ve done with your farm, and I think at least some of today’s young people ’ave a good head on their shoulders.

Text.SourceString: I raised <NPCName>Wakuu</> myself, y’know. His mother, well… Not much to say about her.
Text.LocalizedString: I raised <NPCName>Wakuu</> myself, y’know. His mother, well… Not much to say about her.

Text.SourceString: A fine lass, but she wasn’t around.//<portrait=normal>Ah, never mind. Not worth dredging up the past.
Text.LocalizedString: A fine lass, but she wasn’t around.//<portrait=normal>Ah, never mind. Not worth dredging up the past.

Text.SourceString: I would’ve given <NPCName>Wakuu</> the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. The family business. But he didn’t want any part of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I would’ve given <NPCName>Wakuu</> the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. The family business. But he didn’t want any part of it.

Text.SourceString: No, he wanted to go to college.//There’s dignity in working with yer hands. I tried to tell him that. But does the boy listen to his own father? Bah.
Text.LocalizedString: No, he wanted to go to college.//There’s dignity in working with yer hands. I tried to tell him that. But does the boy listen to his own father? Bah.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> told me he wouldn’t mind if he never sets foot on a boat again.//Breaks my heart, it does.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Wakuu</> told me he wouldn’t mind if he never sets foot on a boat again.//Breaks my heart, it does.

Text.SourceString: He was meant to take the helm of the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> someday. My own flesh and blood.
Text.LocalizedString: He was meant to take the helm of the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</> someday. My own flesh and blood.

Text.SourceString: The sun is out again… This will be good for my lovelies.//Not <NPCName>Wakuu</>. I meant my plants.
Text.LocalizedString: The sun is out again… This will be good for my lovelies.//Not <NPCName>Wakuu</>. I meant my plants.

Text.SourceString: Think it’s probably warm enough for melons now.//Maybe I’ll tell <NPCName>Wakuu</> to pick up some melon seeds next week.
Text.LocalizedString: Think it’s probably warm enough for melons now.//Maybe I’ll tell <NPCName>Wakuu</> to pick up some melon seeds next week.

Text.SourceString: If you want some melons, you gotta wait until next Summer.//Fall isn’t hot enough to grow them.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want some melons, you gotta wait until next Summer.//Fall isn’t hot enough to grow them.

Text.SourceString: Can you still buy seeds at <NPCName>Sam's</>? Might ask <NPCName>Wakuu</> to pick up some for the lighthouse.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you still buy seeds at <NPCName>Sam's</>? Might ask <NPCName>Wakuu</> to pick up some for the lighthouse.

Text.SourceString: Heard there’s some travelers living in the forest who might have some Winter seeds. You know of this person?//<NpcName>Ken</> or something? Not <NpcName>Jack’s</> boy, is it?
Text.LocalizedString: Heard there’s some travelers living in the forest who might have some Winter seeds. You know of this person?//<NpcName>Ken</> or something? Not <NpcName>Jack’s</> boy, is it?

Text.SourceString: Keep seeing weird stuff at the beach nowadays…//Somebody was half naked, sitting by the fireplace from morning till sunset. Bah.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep seeing weird stuff at the beach nowadays…//Somebody was half naked, sitting by the fireplace from morning till sunset. Bah.

Text.SourceString: That’s what warm weather brings out…
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what warm weather brings out…

Text.SourceString: The lighthouse isn’t big enough to grow fruit like papaya.//You can on your farm. They should be in season now.
Text.LocalizedString: The lighthouse isn’t big enough to grow fruit like papaya.//You can on your farm. They should be in season now.

Text.SourceString: Have some leftover blueberries from last season in the freezer. I might make some muffins with them.//My son likes those things, y’know…muffins.
Text.LocalizedString: Have some leftover blueberries from last season in the freezer. I might make some muffins with them.//My son likes those things, y’know…muffins.

Text.SourceString: I can already feel the Summer breeze comin’ in.//Gonna be a hot one this year, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: I can already feel the Summer breeze comin’ in.//Gonna be a hot one this year, I know.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting ready to weed my lovelies. Planting juicy berries next season, I think.//What about yer farm? Berries this Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting ready to weed my lovelies. Planting juicy berries next season, I think.//What about yer farm? Berries this Summer?

Text.SourceString: Harvest Festival, eh? Yeah, I might see it.//<portrait=normal>I don’t like crowds, y’know. But the crops. They might be worth the trip.
Text.LocalizedString: Harvest Festival, eh? Yeah, I might see it.//<portrait=normal>I don’t like crowds, y’know. But the crops. They might be worth the trip.

Text.SourceString: People are gathering on New Year’s Eve, I think… I don’t know, not invited.//My son told me about it.
Text.LocalizedString: People are gathering on New Year’s Eve, I think… I don’t know, not invited.//My son told me about it.

Text.SourceString: It’s all right… Wouldn’t go anyway.//Got nothing to wear.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s all right… Wouldn’t go anyway.//Got nothing to wear.

Text.SourceString: Every time I look at my son, reminds me a bit of his mother. Well…//Same eyes, those two…
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I look at my son, reminds me a bit of his mother. Well…//Same eyes, those two…

Text.SourceString: I wonder how she’s doing now.//<portrait=normal>Don’t tell <NPCName>Wakuu</>. He’s gonna get all sad.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder how she’s doing now.//<portrait=normal>Don’t tell <NPCName>Wakuu</>. He’s gonna get all sad.

Text.SourceString: Gotta keep moving, even old folks like me. It’s good for yer body, yer brain.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta keep moving, even old folks like me. It’s good for yer body, yer brain.

Text.SourceString: A lot of tales on this island… Take it from me. Out of sight, out of mind.//That’s how I live my life.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of tales on this island… Take it from me. Out of sight, out of mind.//That’s how I live my life.

Text.SourceString: Apparently, there used to be harvest people… Small, they are. Come out during harvest season like now.//Planting around the island. I don’t know. Never seen any.
Text.LocalizedString: Apparently, there used to be harvest people… Small, they are. Come out during harvest season like now.//Planting around the island. I don’t know. Never seen any.
